  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean reissue)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; all 13 credibility factors are assessed with achievedLevel meeting or exceeding requiredLevel. One explicitly-flagged low-confidence gap in model-form uncertainty is documented honestly with a detailed rationale and accepted as residual risk supported by conservative bounding analysis. Decision: Accepted.",
