      "rationale": "EXPLICITLY FLAGGED LOW-CONFIDENCE GAP — HONESTLY DOCUMENTED: The power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model (Giersiepen et al. form) has a well-known epistemic uncertainty in the stress exponent (literature range 1.9–2.8). This contributes 62% of total NIH output variance in the Monte Carlo UQ. Confidence in model-form adequacy is explicitly rated LOW. Despite this, the conservative 95th-percentile NIH bound (accounting for full exponent uncertainty range) remains 18% below the clinical threshold. A sensitivity analysis confirmed that even at the upper bound of the exponent range, predictions remain sub-threshold. The gap is accepted as residual risk supported by conservative bounding; the decision record documents this explicitly.",
